{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "WMGT Weekly Tournament Report Generator",
  "description": "Generate comprehensive weekly tournament analysis report with Player of the Week, insights, and statistics",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered",
    "patterns": [
      "**/*"
    ]
  },
  "inputs": [
    {
      "name": "week_code",
      "type": "text",
      "label": "Week",
      "placeholder": "e.g., S18W03",
      "required": true,
      "description": "Enter the tournament week code to analyze"
    }
  ],
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Connect to \"wmgt\" database with sqlcl and analyze Week {{week_code}} tournament results.\n\nGenerate a comprehensive tournament report including:\n\n1. **Top 3 Podium** - Winners with stats and brief performance notes\n2. **Week Statistics** - Total players, countries, score averages, rank distribution, course difficulty analysis\n3. **🌟 Player of the Week** - Someone OUTSIDE top 3 who significantly overperformed their rank (focus on 15+ position improvements vs rank average)\n4. **Hidden Gems & Insights** - Rank upsets, international standouts, course mastery, balanced performances\n5. **Notable Achievements** - Special accomplishments, biggest surprises, fun statistics\n\nAnalysis Guidelines:\n- Focus on stories behind numbers, not just statistics\n- Highlight underdog performances and unexpected results  \n- Use a modest amount of emojis to make it engaging\n- Compare performance vs rank expectations\n- Look for interesting patterns in country/rank performance\n- Celebrate achievements at all levels\n\nKey queries to run:\n- Overall week stats from wmg_tournament_session_points_v\n- Top 10 leaderboard\n- Rank performance analysis (avg position by rank)\n- Overperformers (players significantly above rank average)\n- Country statistics with best performers\n- Special achievements (most balanced, best courses, biggest gaps)\n\nMake it engaging, positive, and highlight the human stories in the data!"
  }
}